All the economy of cocoa based.

00:01:47.540 --> 00:01:51.030
And have you guys heard
about witches' broom?

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.530
I'm not going to go further
about it, but just want to know

00:01:54.530 --> 00:01:57.040
if -- witches' broom,
it's a fungus

00:01:57.040 --> 00:02:00.010
that will attack cacao trees.

00:02:00.010 --> 00:02:01.310
Just a little bit.

00:02:01.310 --> 00:02:03.840
In the '80s or something
like that, my grandfather,

00:02:03.840 --> 00:02:08.130
he had a big plantation
of cacao.

00:02:08.130 --> 00:02:10.740
And then witches' broom
came, which is a fungus,

00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:14.430
and it attack the --
it's quite interesting

00:02:14.430 --> 00:02:16.990
because they attack the
pods, they just turn it

00:02:16.990 --> 00:02:20.730
into a weird color, then
turn into a black color,

00:02:20.730 --> 00:02:23.910
and then just disappear,
the pods.

00:02:23.910 --> 00:02:29.880
So this disease came to Brazil
probably like the late '80s,

00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:33.020
something like that, and
destroyed all the trees,

00:02:33.020 --> 00:02:38.000
pretty much 70% of
the land in this area.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:43.060
Brazil was the first -- the
second actually back then --

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:47.390
largest producer, cocoa
producer, globally.

00:02:47.390 --> 00:02:52.770
So you can think about how
bad that was for the economy.

00:02:52.770 --> 00:02:56.190
And this came up along
with other problems,

00:02:56.190 --> 00:02:58.220
especially inequality.

00:02:58.220 --> 00:03:01.590
You have a lot of social
issues there in this region,

00:03:01.590 --> 00:03:05.620
because they destroy
the whole plantation.

00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:08.250
Now, I'm just sharing
that with you

00:03:08.250 --> 00:03:11.650
because that's how I
started my first contact

00:03:11.650 --> 00:03:14.040
in the cocoa industry.

00:03:14.040 --> 00:03:16.930
And that's why I feel
so passionate about it.

00:03:16.930 --> 00:03:21.400
In Brazil, after this
event, after this happened,

00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:25.620
they tried to find solutions,
of course, to cure this disease.

00:03:25.620 --> 00:03:32.000
And one of them is come up
with disease-resistant trees,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:33.300
cacao trees.

00:03:33.300 --> 00:03:38.320
And one of them, it's
hybrid, seed's hybrid pods,

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:44.100
and [inaudible], which is
kind of like a hybrid --

00:03:44.100 --> 00:03:50.910
actually I think they found
these pods and they just noticed

00:03:50.910 --> 00:03:53.580
that I it's disease-resistant.

00:03:53.580 --> 00:03:56.320
It's exactly what happened
to human beings, right.

00:03:56.320 --> 00:03:59.040
Sometimes disease like
come up and you say, oh,

00:03:59.040 --> 00:04:02.480
this person here has
disease-resistance

00:04:02.480 --> 00:04:04.730
to this disease for some reason,

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:06.030
they don't know how
to explain it.

00:04:06.030 --> 00:04:09.720
But it just use better
technologies to replicate

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:11.890
and use in all the like trees.

00:04:11.890 --> 00:04:18.210
And now that's the kind of seeds
they use in this region to try

00:04:18.210 --> 00:04:21.440
to restore this area,
this cacao area.

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:24.520
And that's one solution
they came up with.

00:04:24.520 --> 00:04:26.570
There is another solution
that I want to talk about,

00:04:26.570 --> 00:04:31.490
it's agroforestry,
agroforestry based, cacao.

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:35.560
Which is you grow
cacao alongside

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:39.690
or inter-crop alongside all
the trees, native trees.

00:04:39.690 --> 00:04:41.960
So for example, you plant cacao,

00:04:41.960 --> 00:04:47.110
and with cacao you plant
banana and [inaudible].

00:04:47.110 --> 00:04:51.490
Have you guys heard
about [inaudible] before?

00:04:51.490 --> 00:04:56.730
Have you? Okay, she's
saying yeah.

