find like different ways

00:31:02.440 --> 00:31:05.320
to adding value to those fruits.

00:31:05.320 --> 00:31:10.570
So they make jelly and sell
like the juice, whatever.

00:31:10.570 --> 00:31:14.520
So the reason I'm saying
that because most of these

00:31:14.520 --> 00:31:17.210
like plantations, they
are agroforestry based.

00:31:17.210 --> 00:31:20.920
And some of them, even though
they're planting the same fruit,

00:31:20.920 --> 00:31:22.220
they have different system.

00:31:22.220 --> 00:31:25.940
So some of them, they use
the fruits like in salad.

00:31:25.940 --> 00:31:28.250
For example, the
main fruit is acai,

00:31:28.250 --> 00:31:29.830
but they have other
fruits like bananas.

00:31:29.830 --> 00:31:32.440
Sometimes they just
take home and eat it.

00:31:32.440 --> 00:31:33.980
Sometimes they're like in salad.

00:31:33.980 --> 00:31:38.090
And so it depends on the farm.

00:31:38.090 --> 00:31:39.390
&gt;&gt; Matthew Dixon: Yeah.

00:31:39.390 --> 00:31:42.580
A lot of the inter-cropping
is not cacao is the focus,

00:31:42.580 --> 00:31:43.920
so the inter-cropping is not

00:31:43.920 --> 00:31:46.860
at like a full sort
of production scale.

00:31:46.860 --> 00:31:50.240
So you see, just like Sam
said, you'll see a little bit

00:31:50.240 --> 00:31:52.740
