00:47:18.660 --> 00:47:22.020
where cacao is grown,
is typically --

00:47:22.020 --> 00:47:26.820
there's not a huge demand
for actual chocolate there.

00:47:26.820 --> 00:47:32.960
The cocoa itself is used
-- it's sold primarily.

00:47:32.960 --> 00:47:36.550
And when it is used in the
home, it's mostly made --

00:47:36.550 --> 00:47:41.970
the pulp is made into drinks or
it's made into other products

00:47:41.970 --> 00:47:43.620
and not exactly chocolate.

00:47:43.620 --> 00:47:47.490
And so what you had
was probably made there

00:47:47.490 --> 00:47:48.910
and it was probably authentic

00:47:48.910 --> 00:47:50.910
and there's probably
nothing wrong with buying it,

00:47:50.910 --> 00:47:52.640
but it probably wasn't
very good.

00:47:52.640 --> 00:47:55.910
Because whoever made it
probably doesn't like chocolate

00:47:55.910 --> 00:48:00.300
and was making it as
